APPLY TO JOIN OUR TEAM!

We welcome students who will be in grades 6-11 at the National School of Physics and Math to apply to join our community as trainees. We also accept applications from students who do not attend NSPhM.

Our expectations of trainees:

  • Trainees maintain high academic performance.
  • Trainees demonstrate full commitment to team activities.
  • Trainees conduct themselves as gracious professionals.

    • We need trainees who are interested in:

  • applying the principles of math, science, and engineering in understanding and designing custom mechanisms
  • using traditional and CNC equipment to fabricate custom parts
  • developing Java code to operate control systems

    • But our team is more than robots. We also need team trainees who are interested in:

  • business functions such as strategic planning, marketing, public relations, fundraising, and accounting
  • media functions such as photography, videography, documentary film making, website development, and social media
  • leading community service activities in support of STEM and non-STEM programs

    • Our team is a great opportunity for highly motivated students who are still searching for "their thing." We are a world-class robotics program, and we compete for the top awards locally, regionally, and internationally. Our students develop their engineering and computer science skills, their business management skills, their communication skills, and their service mindset. Being on our team leads to connections with engineers, computer scientists, university professors, business leaders, and more.

    If you are interested, follow the steps below to learn more about FTC and our team.

  • Watch this video to learn more about FTC
  • Then watch this video about the 2021-2022 FTC robot game: POWERPLAY
  • Click here for the internships application

    • Have any questions? Contact Us

    Email: aenta.team@gmail.com

    Instagram: aenta_team

    TikTok: aenta_team

    Youtube: AENTA Team

    Our Sponsors
